Very tasty despite my substitutions. * Instead of fresh rosemary, I emptied a teabag and put 1 TBSP of dried into the boiling water. * I used a red onion. * Fresh basil replaced the last TBSP of rosemary. * Used leeks instead of shallots * Omitted salt, black pepper, boiling water Also didn't see why you couldn't use the oil from the tomatoes: I did! Barely cooled off, I used a nice slice of organic bread to clean the blender of the extra dip I couldn't get into the storage bowl! Try it!

