I make this all the time and most folks love it. The more you make it, the more you know just how to tweak it to suit your preferences, i.e., I like more lemon. You'll also change the taste depending on amount of sundried, etc. I do, however, agree with earlier review which suggests that it is worth soaking then simmering the dried beans because of the flavor they pick up from rosemary & onions--can't be duplicated with canned. Leftover is divine used as a sandwich spread for turkey, roasted vegetable sandwich, etc.

